Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle to sharp turn of a RHodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '111' Name Ainetor From same die as BM 1987,1110.20.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (1)
